summary: AN ORDINANCE revising the classification plan of the roads and streets of The City of Seattle to reclassify 3rd Avenue from Stewart Street to South Jackson Street as a principal arterial, and 3rd Avenue north of Stewart Street, and a portion of North Northlake Way as minor arterials, authorizing submission of the revised classification plan to the Urban Arterial Board and the Washington State Department of Transportation; and superseding Ordinance 111085.
